<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>43783</id>
    <title>No Post Data with directory based client side SSL certificates and URL rewrite</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Developing using CentOS 5 (Apache2, PHP5, Mysql5) and the Zend Framework which uses the Apache URL 
rewrite engine.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">The closest related bug I could find was 39243.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">However, what appears to be happening is that when the URL rewrite module is used, and you are doing 
SSL client certificate verification based on a location (not for the whole VirtualHost), that no POST data gets 
through, not just posts larger than 128K.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
